  "text": "Moreover, CD16/32 and CD206, specific cell membrane proteins, play an important role in phagocytosis and antigen presentation of the microglia [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . CD16/32 acts as an M1 marker, whereas CD206 is an M2 marker. Our data indicated that betaine inhibited the expression of M1 phenotypic markers and promoted the polarisation of microglia to the M2 phenotype.",
